Users






User roles and permissions


User roles and permissions in AI Defense provide secure and role-specific access to capabilities and insights. Currently, the platform supports two roles: Admin and Analyst.







 




You can manage your AI Defense users and roles in Security Cloud Control. For instructions, see  Managing Role-Based Access Control in the Security Cloud Control user guide.










Roles and permissions


The Admin role provides full system access, including the ability to configure, manage, and control all aspects of AI Defense. Admins can view and modify data, system settings, user roles, and AI Defense features. They have complete authority over validation processes, runtime policies, and application management.

The Analyst role is a management role with restricted access, focused on operational tasks. Analysts can perform validation tests, add applications, and manage assets. However, they do not have the ability to create or modify policies or manage users.


